                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>The subjoined record informs us that certain lands were made tax-free by the great assembly of <hi rend="bold">Uttaramēru-chaturvēdimaṅgalam</hi> in the 2nd year of king <hi rend="bold">Partma</hi> (<hi rend="italic">i.e.</hi>, <hi rend="bold">Pārthivēndra</hi>)-<hi rend="bold">Mahārāja</hi>, ‘who took the head of <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Pāṇḍya</hi>’.</p>
                            
                        </summary>
